<subSubSection id="B601ABBD0AEC78751888983C3A18D752" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="ED952C03ABD788DA88679807B4CFD6F9" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis id="213154956F54C8578C0009BC6FE5CD68" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Etymology.</emphasis>
-
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1CE48314B724C0BC23722026C11DEB68" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
The species is dedicated to Dr. Andrej V. Gorochov for his background work on the taxonomy of crickets in general and of 
<taxonomicName id="FBFB52143F7F0D6F27B48487D833AE27" authorityName="Otte" authorityYear="1983" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Neogryllopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Neogryllopsis" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AA8C0BCCFC609E98C3A29FA811D10F20" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Neogryllopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in particular.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8D50C6ECD4516CE0D8480829436DC0DE" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4A7EF4FBE0A76AD42AA3D80C990A0624" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis id="4191CB9584FE24DC98D56B6494FA995B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
-
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8863BA7CEAD6003CF153D07C993F9778" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
Characters of the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="BB74C99A58AA4FC931CE710581AC0C50" authorityName="Um Nyobe, Kekeunou &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Neogryllopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Neogryllopsis gorochovi" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gorochovi">
<emphasis id="3E3BD30984D96B67796C68A1BA5C1D59" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Neogryllopsis gorochovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Um Nyobe, Kekeunou &amp; Ma 
<emphasis id="3BB135B4E8FB1B4F329B1BFF879ED4EE" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">sp. nov.</emphasis>
grouped it in the 
<emphasis id="9487AE1BCD5A2730BC9F5719F66F8755" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis id="49B145D07BBA08CF0CD814C20028C136" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Sabianus</emphasis>
group
</emphasis>
made up of two species, namely 
<taxonomicName id="552EE90708E0A1D3FC7560A4940F89B0" authorityName="Otte, D., Toms &amp; Cade" authorityYear="1988" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Neogryllopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Neogryllopsis sabianus" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabianus">
<emphasis id="F23A60FB5F79F4B8397393BDB8898A27" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Neogryllopsis sabianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Otte, Toms &amp; Cade, 1988 and 
<taxonomicName id="98914B5A092745368D1EA67002DBB090" authorityName="Otte, D., Toms &amp; Cade" authorityYear="1988" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Neogryllopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Neogryllopsis limpopensis" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limpopensis">
<emphasis id="883887A20C6680B16E56D66D9A9C411F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Neogryllopsis limpopensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Otte, Toms &amp; Cade, 1988. 
<taxonomicName id="D21F38B96C6E507E9DD38D56C1A8AF41" authorityName="Um Nyobe, Kekeunou &amp; Ma" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Neogryllopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Neogryllopsis gorochovi" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gorochovi">
<emphasis id="15BA704A36DB1764D67E66FA788EC738" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Neogryllopsis gorochovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be differentiated from these species by its male genitalia with ectoparamere without setae, short epiphallus, and FW with an undivided round mirror.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4B399782BEBC127DB1B9809DCC5D1F8C" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="description">
<paragraph id="9172C552E1DA003B058394EE75BF9314" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis id="5C05AD313394544F12E86AB098B78172" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Description.</emphasis>
-
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D9C6842BF3BD598DDED6AF6AD4D5141" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
(Figs 
<figureCitation id="008B6C79D8E121AC4E48330DD794B765" captionStart="Fig. 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Fig. 4. Morphology of Neogryllopsis gorochovi sp. nov. A. Male head and pronotum; B. Male lateral view of head and pronotum; C. Male face; D. Female head, pronotum, and FWs; E. Male FW. Scale bars: 7 mm (A); 6 mm (B, E); 5 mm (C); 8 mm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.31.73389.fig4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690969" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="337D18EC20A6F845286EFD074639E0E2" captionStart="Fig. 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Fig. 5. Male genitalia of Neogryllopsis gorochovi sp. nov.; A. Dorsal view; B. Ventral view; C. Drawing. Scale bar: 500 µm. Abbreviations: epiphallus, epi.; ectoparameres, ect.; endoparameres, end.; ramus, r; virga, v.; posterior emargination of epiphallus, p. e. e." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.31.73389.fig5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690970" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">5</figureCitation>
, Table 
<tableCitation id="657528E37AAAEA8E74F29B65AA39D7BC" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Measurements in mm: average + / - standard error (minimum-maximum) total abundance." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/CFE4307320A4B6F615D3B13A128AAE39" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" tableUuid="CFE4307320A4B6F615D3B13A128AAE39">1</tableCitation>
) 
<emphasis id="F95E3A65EF8CB74B38040DA5EE3CBA15" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Male.</emphasis>
Medium size, pale orange-brown. Dorsum of head without a transverse pale band across vertex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="06A0B9335867FB21FC33DBCAF7345CE4" captionStart="Fig. 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Fig. 4. Morphology of Neogryllopsis gorochovi sp. nov. A. Male head and pronotum; B. Male lateral view of head and pronotum; C. Male face; D. Female head, pronotum, and FWs; E. Male FW. Scale bars: 7 mm (A); 6 mm (B, E); 5 mm (C); 8 mm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.31.73389.fig4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690969" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">4A</figureCitation>
); top of head without dark markings along inner margins of eyes; forehead dark brown, without white stripe between lateral ocelli; cheeks pale brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7181EB5550A7C2813CBB57370326FDE8" captionStart="Fig. 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Fig. 4. Morphology of Neogryllopsis gorochovi sp. nov. A. Male head and pronotum; B. Male lateral view of head and pronotum; C. Male face; D. Female head, pronotum, and FWs; E. Male FW. Scale bars: 7 mm (A); 6 mm (B, E); 5 mm (C); 8 mm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.31.73389.fig4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690969" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">4B</figureCitation>
) and face brown before epistomal suture and pale after this suture (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C33190BE273DF8FD2D1197642E57BAB4" captionStart="Fig. 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Fig. 4. Morphology of Neogryllopsis gorochovi sp. nov. A. Male head and pronotum; B. Male lateral view of head and pronotum; C. Male face; D. Female head, pronotum, and FWs; E. Male FW. Scale bars: 7 mm (A); 6 mm (B, E); 5 mm (C); 8 mm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.31.73389.fig4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690969" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">4C</figureCitation>
). Pronotum red-brown without ivory-colored band along margins (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3EE283AB6FF3A7FAB4758944C22F9D03" captionStart="Fig. 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Fig. 4. Morphology of Neogryllopsis gorochovi sp. nov. A. Male head and pronotum; B. Male lateral view of head and pronotum; C. Male face; D. Female head, pronotum, and FWs; E. Male FW. Scale bars: 7 mm (A); 6 mm (B, E); 5 mm (C); 8 mm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.31.73389.fig4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690969" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">4A</figureCitation>
). TI and TII pale, somewhat orange. Hindlegs: FIII with distinct oblique brown stripes on outer surface; TIII pale brown with 5 inner and 5 outer subapical spurs. FWs: dorsum grayish brown, lighter on lateral field; FW length to pronotal length ratio c. 2.3 mm; stridulatory file with 86 teeth; harp with 4 oblique veins; mirror round without a dividing vein; apical field very small (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5E3B0BB864F77513B5A4B072349C2EA2" captionStart="Fig. 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Fig. 4. Morphology of Neogryllopsis gorochovi sp. nov. A. Male head and pronotum; B. Male lateral view of head and pronotum; C. Male face; D. Female head, pronotum, and FWs; E. Male FW. Scale bars: 7 mm (A); 6 mm (B, E); 5 mm (C); 8 mm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.31.73389.fig4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690969" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">4E</figureCitation>
). Hind wings absent. Abdomen: Tergites dark brown, with pale posterior margins; venter light brown; cerci dark brown. Male genitalia (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F50621D47FDCD6A2E411496F29BAB1AC" captionStart="Fig. 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Fig. 5. Male genitalia of Neogryllopsis gorochovi sp. nov.; A. Dorsal view; B. Ventral view; C. Drawing. Scale bar: 500 µm. Abbreviations: epiphallus, epi.; ectoparameres, ect.; endoparameres, end.; ramus, r; virga, v.; posterior emargination of epiphallus, p. e. e." figureDoi="10.3897/jor.31.73389.fig5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/690970" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">5</figureCitation>
): Epiphallus well developed but short; lobes of epiphallus in posterior view long, tapering, two points closely apposed, separated by a deep cleft; lateral lobe of epiphallus with long setae near base and without spines; ectoparamere without setae.
</paragraph>
